{
  "doc_id": "25109",
  "text": "The main application of noble metal nanoparticles is mycotoxins determination. Mycotoxins (aflatoxins, trichothecenes, fumonisins, etc.), produced by mould and other microscopic species, are responsible for acute and chronic toxicity. Mycotoxins can be grouped into four categories, based on their mechanism of action: cytotoxic poisons; neurotoxins; gastrointestinal irritants and toxins that cause symptoms only in association with the ethyl alcohol consumption [CITATION_1] . Mycotoxins usually found in food are accumulated as secondary mould products of the genera Aspergillus, Penicillium and Fusarium [CITATION_2] .",
